public abstract class AndroidCallable<ResultT>
extends Object
implements AndroidCallableI<ResultT>, Runnable

An abstract instance of AndroidCallableI with empty default implementations for onPreCall() and onFinally().

Also implements Runnable so it can be used with any thread or Executor.

See Also:
for some useful default executors.

onPreCall

public void onPreCall()
               throws Exception
Executed in the handler's thread (usually the UI thread) before the task's doInBackground() method is called. Exceptions will be handled by the onException callback.

Specified by:

onFinally

public void onFinally()
Executed in the handler's thread (usually the UI thread) after AndroidCallableI.onSuccess(Object) or AndroidCallableI.onException(Exception) are executed. Always executed iff AndroidCallableI.doInBackground() is executed. Not executed if the task is canceled before it is executed.

Specified by:
onFinally in interface AndroidCallableI<ResultT>
